com.google.android.material.motion.runtime

Class Plan

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.android.material.motion.runtime.Plan
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public abstract class Plan
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    A Plan is an object representing what you want something to do. A Plan uses a Performer to fulfill itself.

    Plans must be Cloneable, and by default clone() makes a shallow copy. If your Plan contains mutable Object references, override clone() to make a deep copy.

    Optional APIs can be implemented by implementing the *Plan interfaces. Libraries that consume Plans can also add optional APIs in its own package.

    See Also:
    The Plan specificiation, Object.clone()
